stork.module.http

Class HTTPBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • stork.module.http.HTTPBuilder

  • public class HTTPBuilder
extends Object
    Sets up HTTPChannel for a HTTPSession. It also maintains multiple states for the session.

    Test state: Collects connection information before initializing the connection. Represented by a Bell, which rings after the test phase is complete.

    Connect state: Be able to start downloading HTTPResource requests. Represented by a Bell, which rings when the test phase is passed, and the connection has been fully established.

    Close state: Rings when this HTTPSession is asked to get closed.

    Keep-alive state: Tells whether the connection can always be open. If this session is able to keep alive, its HTTPChannel would be kept open until a close method is called. Otherwise, its HTTPChannel would be reset for each new HTTPResource.HTTPTap task extracted from the queue waited in this local HTTPBuilder.
